# Problem 

Helping beginning programmers learn how to read code

This project aims to develop tools or resources that guide novice coders through the process of reading and interpreting code, improving their comprehension and confidence in coding tasks.

Statement: University students, particularly those in  STEM majors, are feeling overwhelmed, with their schedules becoming more packed every day, leaving little room for relaxation or enjoyment. With Ever changing and evolving technology students in STEM need to spend extra time learning the new technologies for their majors. New technologies such as Improved or new programs like Constantly Learning new technologies takes extra time out of those students' days leaving little time for other activities. 

# Prior Solutions

## Interactive textbook

The interactive textbook helps to learn code by having small sections of text, followed by an interactive code example of what was inside the previous section of text. Then looping this process until at the end an assignment to put into use the above information.  

Instead of giving full examples immediately, we are going to give the option to either attempt a similar problem to that of the example they are being shown, or to have the example problem be done for them with a step by step visual process. This is so that the user can determine where they are skill wise, based on the difficulty of the similar problem or the difficulty following along with the example.

## Solution 2

1. Providing clear, step-by-step explanations of code structures and logic.  
2. Introducing interactive exercises where learners practice reading and interpreting code snippets.  
3. Offering a feedback mechanism to correct misconceptions and guide learners through common programming patterns.

The App emphasizes breaking down code structures, logic, and flow through clear, step-by-step explanations. The feedback mechanism offers personalized guidance, helping beginners identify and correct their misconceptions early on

 

## Solution 3

# Overview:

IntuiCode is designed to support beginner programmers in learning how to read and interpret code, while also improving their programming skills. By offering interactive tools and resources, the application provides users with step by step guidance, code examples, and feedback on their programs. Some key features include an integrated code editor, contextual explanations, and interactive quizzes. The app breaks down coding concepts into more manageable tasks, allowing the user to progress at their own pace. Additionally, the interactive problems and quizzes reinforce learning by providing instant feedback for the user.

**Immediate feedback** is An important tool for beginners, For other similar apps not alot have this feature. Immediate feedback lets users get feedback on their errors or flaws in their thinking allowing for quicker and more effective learning.  
	**overwhelming complexity** is another major Issue with beginners. Our app breaks down the Tasks into step by step guidance. Allowing users to understand the smaller underlying things that made it complex and demystifying it.    
	 **Interactive practice** When first learning to code many sources do not have much , or if there is there are extra steps to be able to do it. Our app has A built-in code editor that allows for users to be able to run and experiment with code as they are reading/learning from it. Allowing for better learning as well as built in challenges to help them practice. These challenges can vary from, either writing a small program to do a small task, being given a section of code and to find the error, or a simple multiple choice game that will prompt the user for the best fit in the section of code. Practice problems will also be similar to this format, all with varying levels of difficulty based on the users level.
